ylvania|publisher=Friends' Book Association|year=1884|lccn=04013085|oclc=79879919|accessdate=2016-01-16|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n**{{cite journal|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_3opAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA729#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Book Notice: Banneker, ''the Afric-American Astronomer.'' From the posthumous papers of M.E. Tyson. Edited by Her Daughter. Phila. 1020 Arch Street. 1884||work=Friends Review: A Religious, Literary and Miscellaneous Journal|volume=37|number=46|page=729|editor=Hartshorne, Henry|location=1316 Filbert Street, Philadelphia|publisher=Franklin E. Paige|date=1884-06-21|accessdate=2017-01-16|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n{{Clear}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{Appletons' Poster|year=1900|Banneker, Benjamin|Benjamin Banneker}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Benjamin Banneker}}\n* {{Librivox author |id=8188}}\n* {{cite book|last=Bragg|first=George F., Jr.|year=1914|title=Benjamin Banneker|url=https://archive.org/stream/menofmaryland00brag#page/28/mode/2up|work=Men of Maryland| publisher=Church Advocate Press, Baltimore, Maryland|pages=29\u201334|oclc=4346580|accessdate=2010-02-01|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite web|last1=O'Connor|first1=John J.|last2=Robertson|first2=Edmund F.|author-link2=Edmund F. Robertson|url=http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Banneker.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312001149/http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Banneker.html|archivedate=2016-03-12|title=Benjamin Banneker|work=[[MacTutor History of Mathematics archive]]|publisher=[[University of St Andrews]] School of Mathematics and Statistics|location=[[St Andrews]], [[Fife]], [[Scotland]]|date=May 2000|accessdate=2016-11-29}}\n* {{cite web|author=Phoenix Films, Inc.|year=1981|url=https://archive.org/details/themanwholovedthestarsreel2|title=The Man Who Loved the Stars|format=video|work= [[Docudrama]] starring [[Ossie Davis]] (59:11 minutes)|publisher= Cinemonde International, Ltd.|accessdate