>{{cite web|url=https://bengalswire.usatoday.com/2019/02/21/aj-miranda-green-welcome-second-son-gunnar-blaze/|title=A.J., Miranda Green welcome second son, Gunnar Blaze, to the world|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.bengals.com/team/roster/A.J.-Green/d1e7b054-2722-4a10-9dad-687267489bd5 Cincinnati Bengals bio]\n* [http://www.georgiadogs.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/green_aj00.html Georgia Bulldogs bio]\n\n{{2011 NFL Draft}}\n{{BengalsFirstPick}}\n{{Bengals2011DraftPicks}}\n{{Cincinnati Bengals roster navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Green, A. J.}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American football wide receivers]]\n[[Category:Cincinnati Bengals players]]\n[[Category:Georgia Bulldogs football players]]\n[[Category:American Conference Pro Bowl players]]\n[[Category:Unconferenced Pro Bowl players]]\n[[Category:Under Armour All-American football players]]\n[[Category:People from Summerville, South Carolina]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from South Carolina]]\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A._J._Green"}
{"title_page": "Bang Wa BTS station", "text_new": "{{Infobox station\n| name = Bang Wa\n| native_name = \u0e1a\u0e32\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e49\u0e32\n| native_name_lang = th\n| type = {{rint|bangkok|Silom}} {{rint|bangkok|blue}}\n| former = \n| opened = 5 December 2013 (BTS Skytrain) <ref name=\"opening\">{{cite web |url=http://www.dailynews.co.th/Content/bangkok/126958/5\u0e18.\u0e04.\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e1a\u0e35\u0e17\u0e35\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e2a\u0e27\u0e34\u0e48\u0e07\u0e1f\u0e23\u0e35\u0e16\u0e36\u0e07\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e49\u0e32-\u0e40\u0e23\u0e34\u0e48\u0e21\u0e40\u0e01\u0e47\u0e1a\u0e04\u0e48\u0e32\u0e42\u0e14\u0e22\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e2316\u0e21.\u0e04.57 |script-title=th:\u0e02\u0e36\u0e49\u0e19\u0e1a\u0e35\u0e17\u0e35\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e2a\u0e44\u0e1b\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1f\u0e23\u0e35\u0e16\u0e36\u0e07 16 \u0e21.\u0e04. 57 |last= |first= |date=20 August 2012 |accessdate=21 June 2014 |language=Thai |trans-title=Free extension cost for riding to Bang Wa until 16 January 2014|work=[[Daily News (Thailand)|Daily News]]}}</ref> <br/> 24 August 2019 (MRT Blue Line) <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://coconuts.co/bangkok/news/visit-2-more-mrt-blue-line-stops-free-starting-saturday/|title=Visit 2 more MRT Blue Line stops free starting Saturday {{!}} Coconuts Bangkok|last=coconutsbangkok|date=2019-08-23|website=Coconuts|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.bemplc.co.th/Metro-News-Detail?id=10172|title=\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e34\u0e14\u0e43\u0e2b\u0e49\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e0a\u0e32\u0e0a\u0e19\u0e17\u0e14\u0e25\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e43\u0e0a\u0e49\u0e1a\u0e23\u0e34\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e23\u0e16\u0e44\u0e1f\u0e1f\u0e49\u0e32 \u0e2a\u0e32\u0e22\u0e2a\u0e35\u0e19\u0e49\u0e33\u0e40\u0e07\u0e34\u0e19\u0e2a\u0e48\u0e27\u0e19\u0e15\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e02\u0e22\u0e32\u0e22|website=metro.bemplc.co.th|language=th|access-date=2019-08-25}}</ref>\n| image = Bang Wa stn. 2019-09 (3).jpg\n| image_caption = Mezzanine of a station with BTS platform in the background\n| address = [[Phasi Charoen District|Phasi Charoen]], [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]]\n| owned = [[Bangkok Metropolitan Administration]] (BMA) <br/> [[Mass Rapid Transit Authority of Thailand]] (MRTA)\n| operator = [[BTS Group Holdings|Bangkok Mass Transit System<br>Public Company Limited]] (BTSC) <br/> [[Bangkok Expressway and Metro Public Company Limited]] (BEM)\n| coordinates = {{coord|13|43|14.25|N|100|27|28.33|E|region:TH_type:railwaystation|display=inline,title}}\n| line = {{plain list|\n*{{rail color box|system=BTS|line=Silom}} }} </br> [[MRT Blue Line]]\n| code = [[Silom line]]: S12 </br> [[MRT Blue Line]]: BL34\n| services = {{s-rail|title=Bangkok Rapid Transit}}\n{{s-line|system=BTS|line=Silom|previous=Wutthakat|type=West|type2=South}}\n{{s-line|system=Bangkok MRT|line=MRT Blue|previous=Bang Phai|next=Phetkasem 48|type=West|type2=North|transfer=Bang Wa}}\n}}\n'''Bang Wa station''' ({{lang-th|\u0e2a\u0e16\u0e32\u0e19\u0e35\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e49\u0e32}}, {{RTGS|''Sathani Bang Wa''}}, {{IPA-th|s\u0101.t\u02b0\u01ce\u02d0.n\u012b\u02d0 b\u0101\u02d0\u014b w\u00e2\u02d0|pron}}) is a rapid transit station on the [[Silom Line]] and [[MRT Blue Line]] in [[Phasi Charoen District]], [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]]. The station is located on an intersection between  Ratchaphruek Road and [[Phet Kasem Road]]. It is surrounded by residences, small shops and office towers. Station serves as a interchange station for Silom Line and MRT Blue Line, provided direct interchange but separate fare and ticket between 2 Lines.\n\n<br />\n\n== BTS section ==\nBang Wa station opened on 5 December 2013, the same day as the opening of [[Wutthakat station]]<ref name=\"opening\" />. The station served as a terminus for Silom Line since.<gallery>\nFile:201701 Ticket Barriers at Bang Wa Station.jpg|Ticket Hall of BTS Silom Line\nFile:201701 Platforms of Bang Wa Station.jpg|Silom Line platform\nFile:201701 Train No.108 at Bang Wa Station.jpg|Silom Line Platform\nFile:Transfer area at Bang Wa Station (BTS Side) 2.jpg|Transfer hall\nFile:BTS Bang Wa stn.JPG|Station entrance\nFile:BTS S12 Traditional station sign.svg|Bang Wa station traditional sign (BTS) before the opening of MRT\nFile:BTS S12 Traditional station sign (Interchange MRT).svg|Bang Wa station traditional sign (BTS) after the opening of MRT\n</gallery>\n\n== MRT section ==\nThe MRT section of a station opened on 24 August 2019 as part of a Blue Line extenstion.<br /><gallery>\nFile:Bang Wa MRT Station (under construction), June 2016.jpg|MRT section underconstruction (Photo taken from BTS platform)\nFile:Bang Wa stn. 2019-09 (2).jpg|Ticket Hall of MRT Blue Line\nFile:Platform level Bang Wa Station.jpg|Blue Line Platform\nFile:Transfer hall Bang Wa Station (MRT Side) 3.jpg|Transfer hall\nFile:MRT BL34 Traditional station sign.svg|Bang Wa station traditional sign (MRT)\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n\n*[[Bangkok Skytrain]]\n*[[MRT (Bangkok)]]\n\n<br />{{Bangkok Rapid Transit stations|Blue=yes|Silom=yes}}\n\n[[Category:BTS Skytrain stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 2013]]\n\n\n{{Bangkok-geo-stub}}\n{{Thailand-rail-transport-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox station\n| name = Bang Wa\n| native_name = \u0e1a\u0e32\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e49\u0e32\n| native_name_lang = th\n| type = {{rint|bangkok|Silom}} {{rint|bangkok|blue}}\n| former = \n| opened = 5 December 2013 (BTS Skytrain) <ref name=\"opening\">{{cite web |url=http://www.dailynews.co.th/Content/bangkok/126958/5\u0e18.\u0e04.\u0e19\u0e35\u0e49\u0e1a\u0e35\u0e17\u0e35\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e2a\u0e27\u0e34\u0e48\u0e07\u0e1f\u0e23\u0e35\u0e16\u0e36\u0e07\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e49\u0e32-\u0e40\u0e23\u0e34\u0e48\u0e21\u0e40\u0e01\u0e47\u0e1a\u0e04\u0e48\u0e32\u0e42\u0e14\u0e22\u0e2a\u0e32\u0e2316\u0e21.\u0e04.57 |script-title=th:\u0e02\u0e36\u0e49\u0e19\u0e1a\u0e35\u0e17\u0e35\u0e40\u0e2d\u0e2a\u0e44\u0e1b\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e49\u0e32\u0e1f\u0e23\u0e35\u0e16\u0e