n'''Bang Wa station''' ({{lang-th|\u0e2a\u0e16\u0e32\u0e19\u0e35\u0e1a\u0e32\u0e07\u0e2b\u0e27\u0e49\u0e32}}, {{RTGS|''Sathani Bang Wa''}}, {{IPA-th|s\u0101.t\u02b0\u01ce\u02d0.n\u012b\u02d0 b\u0101\u02d0\u014b w\u00e2\u02d0|pron}}) is a rapid transit station on the [[Silom Line]] and [[MRT Blue Line]] in [[Phasi Charoen District]], [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]]. The station is located on an intersection between  Ratchaphruek Road and [[Phet Kasem Road]]. It is surrounded by residences, small shops and office towers. Station serves as a interchange station for Silom Line and MRT Blue Line, provided direct interchange but separate fare and ticket between 2 Lines.\n\n<br />\n\n== BTS section ==\nBang Wa station opened on 5 December 2013, the same day as the opening of [[Wutthakat station]]<ref name=\"opening\" />. The station served as a terminus for Silom Line since.<gallery>\nFile:201701 Ticket Barriers at Bang Wa Station.jpg|Ticket Hall of BTS Silom Line\nFile:201701 Platforms of Bang Wa Station.jpg|Silom Line platform\nFile:201701 Train No.108 at Bang Wa Station.jpg|Silom Line Platform\nFile:Transfer area at Bang Wa Station (BTS Side) 2.jpg|Transfer hall\nFile:BTS Bang Wa stn.JPG|Station entrance\nFile:BTS S12 Traditional station sign.svg|Bang Wa station traditional sign (BTS) before the opening of MRT\nFile:BTS S12 Traditional station sign (Interchange MRT).svg|Bang Wa station traditional sign (BTS) after the opening of MRT\n</gallery>\n\n== MRT section ==\nThe MRT section of a station opened on 24 August 2019 as part of a Blue Line extenstion.<br /><gallery>\nFile:Bang Wa MRT Station (under construction), June 2016.jpg|MRT section underconstruction (Photo taken from BTS platform)\nFile:Bang Wa stn. 2019-09 (2).jpg|Ticket Hall of MRT Blue Line\nFile:Platform level Bang Wa Station.jpg|Blue Line Platform\nFile:Transfer hall Bang Wa Station (MRT Side) 3.jpg|Transfer hall\nFile:MRT BL34 Traditional station sign.svg|Bang Wa station traditional sign (MRT)\n</gallery>\n\n==